<p>Question is : The string "PAYPALISHIRING" is written in a zigzag pattern on a given number of rows like this: (you may want to display this pattern in a fixed font for better legibility)</p>  <pre><code>P   A   H   N A P L S I I G Y   I   R </code></pre>  <p>And then read line by line: "PAHNAPLSIIGYIR"</p>  <p>I have written below code, appearantly it works fine, but I might miss some corner cases. Could you help me to find all the corner cases for this question on my answer?</p>  <pre><code>public static String zigZagConversion(String s , int rowNum){      if (s == null){         throw new IllegalArgumentException();     }     if (rowNum == 1){         return s;     }     StringBuilder str = new StringBuilder();      int step = 2 * rowNum - 2 ;      for (int i = 0 ; i &lt; rowNum ; i++){          if( i == 0 || i == rowNum -1){              for (int j = i ; j &lt; s.length() ; j +=step){                  str.append(s.charAt(j));                                 }                        }          else{              int step2 = 2* (rowNum - i - 1);             int step3 = step - step2;             int k = i;             boolean flag = true;              while (k &lt; s.length()){                 str.append(s.charAt(k));                  if(flag){                                            k += step2;                     flag = false;                 }                 else{                                            k +=step3;                    flag = false;                 }              }                         }     } return str.toString();       } </code></pre>